I don’t know who said it but I fully agree: Life is about the MOMENTS, the ADVENTURES you create! 

One of our favorite things things to do as a family is visit The Happiest Place on Earth. We love making MAGICAL MEMORIES there. A few weeks ago, we stayed @hojoanaheim in a room with a pool view. It was spectacular. This hotel has a retro vibe plus you can see iconic @disneyland sites like The Monorail, The Matterhorn, and Space Mountain FROM the hotel. It’s a short 8 minute walk too. 

Do yourself a favor, book the trip(s), AND book your vacation (or staycation) @hojoanaheim 
✨➡️ ✨ If you click the link in my bio, you’ll find a discount for you! ✨⬅️✨

Now happy memory making, friend! 😁

I’ve been in Yoga Camp the last 5 days @ivystandardyoga 🧘‍♀️ 

Yesterday, I faced a major fear: Handstand. With guidance from @benjamin.sears + assistance from @cynwehr & @msaldivar_1 I was able to get into my first handstand ever. I lost it after (balled my eyes out) - all the emotions uncontrollably came out & released. I felt embarrassed for crying, still afraid, shaken up, proud of myself for showing up to the class (because my inner voice was telling me - don’t go, you can’t do a headstand, you can’t do handstand?!), BUT PROUD of myself for doing it. After my cry session, I asked Cynthia and Mya to assist me two more times. Two more successes. 

Thank you for this space: to face fears, to feel, to accept, to grow. 

I was able to take two Ashtanga classes with @charmony_yogi - her cueing is so clear + calm. I was SO sore after but I’m eager to try this yoga again. The 108 & Integrative Hatha Yoga classes by @brandylynyoga were challenging + inspiring. I love watching her and the other advanced students - I have so much work to do in these classes. I appreciate the opportunity for growth & to push myself. @luxyoga and the headstand workshop with @benjamin.sears had its own challenges I had never faced before - it was nice to experience a more open teaching vibe and was incredibly informative. The 26&2 Masterclasses from @cynwehr were fabulously helpful. In yesterday’s 26&2 class, I borrowed some of @hotyogarachel & @brandylynyoga energy during some of my poses that usually get to my head: Standing Forehead to Knee + Bow Pulling Pose. I was proud of my efforts and how I found those poses, where I usually fall out. A win for me. Cynthia’s calm voice, cues, and gentle reminders really helped. 

Thank you, @ivystandardyoga for helping me develop these skills, allowing the space to improve, for the challenge, space to discover more of myself and my practice, and gain more knowledge. I have a lot of work to do and will continue this path of learning. 

I’m so happy we experienced this together, Mya & Sloan. 💕💕

#yogacamp #ivystandardyoga #hotyoga #26and2 #suvitahotyoga #yoga

I was obsessed with bunnies when I was young. I had my mom stencil bunnies along the border of my room. When I’d show people my collection of bunnies, I’d point out every single one of them, including every 3” stenciled bunny spaced 2” apart from one another. 

For a while we had two bunnies as pets: Jenny & Snowy. I named Jenny after my best friend at the time. 

This last weekend we went down to my parent’s house so I could plant her flowers. It was our first trip in our EV and we stumbled upon this little petting zoo by one of the charging areas. They had really cute animals. I was shocked to walk around the corner and see a camel 🐪 😳. I REALLY wanted this bunny. 😍🐰

That’s all folks! 🥕 🐇😉

Thump if you get it.

Every night Clint and I take a garden walk together. 🪻🌹🌸🌼🌷It’s one of my favorite things to do; it’s our time to chat about our day, calm the mind, play with Piper (because she has to join 🦊), and talk to my garden babies. I get so excited to see my plants grow and make plans for our yard. 
A few years ago, I had to take out my beloved heart bush because it was dying. I was stuck for a while on what to plant there at the center of our house. But at one of my recent trips to @glovernursery to buy some climbing roses for my new arbor, I discovered they had a new variety of hydrangea I’ve been eyeing online. Every night, we check on this new addition and talk her up. ✨🤍✨ 

I have a small area I’d like to plant next. Should I add another hydrangea? 

#disney #uphouse #gardening #plantmom #gardenaesthetic #disneyhouse #stopandsmelltheroses
